comments.body:
To be honest, this part of code is inherited directly from the previous version, kept untouched to preserve compatibility. This `keyLabel` is also only used in generating `keyboard_maps.dart`, a file unused by the hardware keyboard API and to be removed after the deprecation window. `LogicalKeyboardKey.keyLabel` is defined differently (after the last round of change to it) and also generated differently.

I'm adding the following doc to `LogicalKeyEntry.keyLabel`:
```
  /// A string indicating the letter on the keycap of a letter key.
  ///
  /// This is only used to generate the key label mapping in keyboard_map.dart.
  /// [LogicalKeyboardKey.keyLabel] uses a different definition and is generated
  /// differently.
```

